<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 5:01PM CST  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Perry and northern
Stone Counties through 600 PM CST...
At 459 PM CST, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated
strong thunderstorms along a line extending from 4 miles southeast of
Sunrise to 7 miles southwest of Maxie. Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Richton, Beaumont and New Augusta.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
